message.content: The most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and question answering. Other likely sub-categories include "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as reinforcement learning is used, "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) as the paper discusses information retrieval techniques, "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as the paper uses policy gradient for training, and "cs.CY" (Computers and Society) as the paper discusses the implications of the language learned by the agent.
